==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*raedanan'', from Indo-European ''*rei-'' ‘reason, count’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[radan|rādan]] (Dutch [[raden]]), Old High German [[ratan|rātan]] (German [[raten]]), Old Norse [[ráða]] (Swedish [[råda]]), Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐍂𐌴𐌳𐌰𐌽]].  The Indo-European root is also the source of Greek [[αριθμος]], Old Irish [[immrádim]], Old Church Slavonic ''raditi''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈræ:dan/}}

